ğŸ”§ How They Work in Your Code
jsx
Copy
Edit
// MoviesApp.test.jsx
import { render, screen, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react'; // â† RTL
import { MoviesApp } from './MoviesApp';

describe('MoviesApp', () => {
  test('adds a movie to the list', () => {
    render(<MoviesApp />);                               // â† RTL renders component
    fireEvent.change(screen.getByPlaceholderText('Enter Movie Name'), {
      target: { value: 'Inception' }
    });                                                   // â† RTL simulates input
    fireEvent.click(screen.getByText('Add to Watchlist')); // â† RTL simulates click
    expect(screen.getByText('Inception')).toBeInTheDocument(); // â† Jest asserts result
  });
});
âš™ï¸ package.json (important dependencies)
json
Copy
Edit
"devDependencies": {
  "jest": "^29.x",                    // â† Test runner
  "@testing-library/react": "^14.x", // â† RTL core
  "@testing-library/jest-dom": "^6.x", // â† Custom Jest matchers (e.g. toBeInTheDocument)
  "@testing-library/user-event": "^14.x" // â† Better than fireEvent for user actions
}
ğŸ§© Summary
Tool	Responsibility
Jest	Run tests, provide expect
React Testing Library	Render component, interact with DOM
jest-dom	Adds matchers like toBeInTheDocument
user-event	Simulates realistic user behavior

